
======================================================================
1. E8 THETA FUNCTION COEFFICIENTS
======================================================================

E8 theta function: Theta_{E8}(q) = 1 + 240*Sigma sigma_3(n)*q^n
Also equals E_4(q), the weight-4 Eisenstein series for SL(2,Z)

First coefficients a(n) = 240*sigma_3(n) for n >= 1:
   n   sigma_3(n)    a(n)=240*s3                       factored
----------------------------------------------------------------------
   0            0              1  1 (constant term)
   1            1            240  240 = #roots(E8)
   2            9           2160  240 * KEY2^2 = 2160
   3           28           6720  240 * C(8,2) = 6720
   4           73          17520  240 * 73
   5          126          30240  240 * 126
   6          252          60480  240 * 252
   7          344          82560  240 * 344
   8          585         140400  240 * 585
   9          757         181680  240 * 757
  10         1134         272160  240 * 1134
  11         1332         319680  240 * 1332
  12         2044         490560  240 * 2044
  13         2198         527520  240 * 2198
  14         3096         743040  240 * 3096
  15         3528         846720  240 * 3528
  16         4681        1123440  240 * 4681
  17         4914        1179360  240 * 4914
  18         6813        1635120  240 * 6813
  19         6860        1646400  240 * 6860
  20         9198        2207520  240 * 9198

Key values:
  a(0) = 1
  a(1) = 240 = #roots(E8) = V(icos)*V(dodec)
  a(2) = 240*9 = 240*KEY2^2 = 2160
  a(3) = 240*28 = 240*C(8,2) = 6720
  a(4) = 240*73 = 17520
  a(5) = 240*126 = 30240

  sigma_3(2) = 1+8 = 9 = KEY2^2
  sigma_3(3) = 1+27 = 28 = C(rank(E8), 2)
  sigma_3(5) = 1+125 = 126 = C(9,4) = C(KEY2^2, rank(F4))
  sigma_3(6) = 1+8+27+216 = 252 = C(10,5) = C(V(Petersen), KEY1+KEY2)
                                         = |tau(3)| from Ramanujan!

