======================================================================

======================================================================
THETA/MODULAR TOURNAMENT DICTIONARY
======================================================================

Modular form                    Value          Tournament/Lie
----------------------------------------------------------------------
E_4 leading coeff               240            #roots(E8)
E_6 leading coeff               504            7*72 = H_forb_1*sigma(30)
504/240                         21/10          H_forb_2/V(Petersen)
1728 = E_4^3/Delta norm         12^3           h(E6)^3
j-inv constant term             744            |BT|*(h(E8)+1)
j-inv q coeff                   196884         dim(V_Monster)+1
sigma_3(2)                      9              KEY2^2
sigma_3(3)                      28             C(rank(E8),2)
sigma_3(6)                      252            C(V(Petersen),5) = |tau(3)|
PSL(2,Z)                        Z/2*Z/3        Z/KEY1 * Z/KEY2
|PSL(2,5)|                      60             |A5| = |BI|/2
|PSL(2,7)|                      168            H_forb_1*|BT|
N(f(omega)) in Z[omega]         91             Phi3(KEY1)*Phi3(KEY2)
Discriminant exponent           24             |BT|
r_8/E8 ratio                    15             C(h(G2),2)

The deepest connection: PSL(2,Z) = Z/KEY1 * Z/KEY2
The entire theory of modular forms is built on the free product
of the two tournament keys.
